Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on planning contact sequences for humanoid robots, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a learning-based approach for predicting the dynamic evolution of the robot centroidal momenta, which can be considered as an application of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to learn the prediction of the robot centroidal momenta. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - Although not the main focus of the paper, computer vision techniques may be used for perception and environment modeling, which are important for contact planning. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with planning dynamically robust contact sequences, which can be considered as a control problem.
